      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GENERAL LINCOLN (8) settled close to the pace the went to the front and finished too well to win for the second time in a row last start over 1720m at this track, getting there by 1.4 metres. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. Meets a comparable field and he can add to his recent outstanding results. TRIED AND TRUSTED (2) produced a strong performance last start when he battled on bravely to just miss out over 1609m at Newcastle. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Meets a similar line up and he can figure in the finish. TIGERLICIOUS (6) is worth some thought after her last-start fifth over 1720m at this track. TIME TO DANCE NZ (10) can continue the good form.",
